post-operative value was 98.3 (range 85-100). The Quick-DASH mean post-operative 
value was 2.5 (range 0-9.1) with a mean improvement of 41.4 points (range 
36.4-47.7 points). All patients resumed sports in 6 months post-operatively.
CONCLUSIONS: The autologous transplant of an osteochondral plug is a safe and 
promising procedure. Despite being more demanding, the arthroscopic approach is 
a valuable tool if the surgeon aims to reduce the invasiveness of the procedure, 
with all the consequent advantages.
LEVEL OF EVIDENCE IV: Retrospective case series, therapeutic study.

