concentrations. The final model was evaluated in a fourth independent cohort and 
has an AUC = 0.94, PPV = 0.92, sensitivity = 0.85 and specificity = 0.93 for 
detection of ovarian cancer stages I-IV. The novel plasma protein signature 
could be used to improve the diagnosis of women with adnexal ovarian mass or in 
screening to identify women that should be referred to specialized examination.

